ABCD
(O)
AB=a, BC=b, CD=c, AD=d, AC=x, BD=y
\frac{x}{y}=\frac{ad+bc}{ab+cd}
S_{ABC}=\frac{1}{2}ab\sin B
\frac{x}{2R}=\sin B
S_{ABC}=\frac{1}{2}ab\frac{x}{2R}
S_{ADC}=\frac{1}{2}cd \sin D
\sin D=\sin (\pi - B) = \sin B = \frac{x}{2R}.
S_{ABCD}=\frac{x}{4R}(ab+cd)
S_{ABCD}=\frac{y}{4R}(ad+cb)
\frac{x}{4R}(ab+cd) = \frac{y}{4R}(ad+cb)
